Definition: the reasoning involved in drawing a conclusion or making a logical judgment on the basis of circumstantial evidence and prior conclusions rather than on the basis of direct observation
Synonyms: adj, all, deductive, inferential, connotative, pert, verb, communication, infer, cognition, illation, reasoning, the, involved, in, drawing, a, conclusion, or, making, logical, judgment, on, basis, of, circumstantial, evidence, and, prior, conclusions, rather, than, direct, observation
Category: noun.cognition
